            <mods:abstract>In this essay, bell hooks praises how Lemonade has shifted the mainstream’s gaze toward black female bodies (though, possibly exploits them), but criticizes how Beyonce’s rage and destruction celebrate violence. Dr. hooks argues that some messages shine through, like making lemons into lemonade, but others wind up hurting women, specifically black women. It’s a well-rounded critique that started more conversations surrounding Lemonade’s impact.</mods:abstract>
